  "prompt": "I'm on Jio network. I am able to watch Youtube videos cleanly without much buffering but downloading speed is pathetic",
  "response": "It sounds like you might be experiencing network congestion or throttling issues. Here are a few steps to help improve your downloading speed on the Jio network:\n\n1. **Check Signal Strength**: Make sure you have a strong signal. Poor signal strength can cause slow download speeds.\n\n2. **Network Settings**:\n   - Go to your phone\u2019s network settings and make sure you are connected to the fastest network available.\n   - Ensure your device is set to use LTE/4G only if available.\n\n3. **Restart Devices**: Sometimes, simply restarting your smartphone or modem/router can resolve speed issues.\n\n4. **APN Settings**: Ensure your Access Point Name (APN) settings are correct. The APN for Jio network should be \u201cjionet\u201d.\n\n5. **Data Usage**: Check if you have exceeded your data cap which may result in throttling by your network provider.\n\n6. **Background Apps**: Close any background apps that might be using up bandwidth.\n\n7. **Download Managers**: Consider using a download manager. These tools can sometimes optimize your downloads and provide better speeds.\n\n8. **VPN**: In some cases, using a VPN can help bypass potential throttling by your ISP.\n\n9. **Customer Support**: If the problem persists, contact Jio's customer support for assistance. They can check for any network issues in your area.\n\nIf you're able to stream videos smoothly but face issues while downloading files, it might indicate network management practices by your ISP that prioritize streaming traffic over file downloads. Contacting customer support could provide you with more personalized solutions.",
